K-means clustering en fonction de la valeur client

In [10]:
values = df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'].values.reshape(-1, 1)
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=2, random_state=0).fit(values)
thresholds = np.sort(kmeans.cluster_centers_.flatten())
kde = gaussian_kde(df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'])
x = np.linspace(df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'].min(), df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'].max(), 1000)
kde_values = kde(x)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(x, kde_values, color='skyblue', label='Density', linewidth=2)
plt.fill_between(x, 0, kde_values, where=(x <= thresholds[0]), color='lightgreen', alpha=0.5, label='Segment 1')
plt.fill_between(x, 0, kde_values, where=((x > thresholds[0]) & (x <= thresholds[1])), color='mediumseagreen', alpha=0.5, label='Segment 2')
plt.fill_between(x, 0, kde_values, where=(x > thresholds[1]), color='darkgreen', alpha=0.5, label='Segment 3')
for threshold in thresholds:
    plt.axvline(x=threshold, linestyle='--', linewidth=2, color='black', label=f'Threshold ({threshold:.2f})')
offset = 200
plt.scatter(thresholds, [kde_values.max() * 0.05] * len(thresholds), color='black', zorder=5)
plt.text(thresholds[0] + offset, kde_values.max() * 0.05, f'{thresholds[0]:.2f}', fontsize=14, color='black', ha='left', weight='bold')
plt.text(thresholds[1] + offset, kde_values.max() * 0.05, f'{thresholds[1]:.2f}', fontsize=14, color='black', ha='left', weight='bold')
plt.text(thresholds[0] / 2, kde_values.max() * 0.5, 'Low Value', fontsize=15, color='black', ha='center', weight='bold', rotation='vertical')
plt.text((thresholds[0] + thresholds[1]) / 2, kde_values.max() * 0.5, 'Medium Value', fontsize=15, color='black', ha='center', weight='bold', rotation='vertical')
plt.text(thresholds[1] + (x.max() - thresholds[1]) / 2, kde_values.max() * 0.5, 'High Value', fontsize=15, color='black', ha='center', weight='bold', rotation='vertical')
plt.title('Segmentation client avec K-means clustering', fontsize=14, weight='bold')
plt.xlabel('Valeur Client', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Nombre de Clients', fontsize=14)
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
conditions = [
    (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] <= thresholds[0]),
    (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] > thresholds[0]) & (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] <= thresholds[1]),
    (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] > thresholds[1])]
In [5]:
labels = ['Segment 1', 'Segment 2', 'Segment 3']
df_positive['Segment'] = np.select(conditions, labels, default='Unknown')
segment_summary = df_positive.groupby('Segment')['VALEUR_CLIENT'].agg(['count', 'mean']).rename(columns={'count': 'Nombre de Clients', 'mean': 'Valeur Client Moyenne'})
churn_summary = df_positive.groupby('Segment')['A_RENOUVELLE'].apply(lambda x: (x == False).mean()).rename('Taux de Churn')
combined_summary = segment_summary.join(churn_summary)
formatted_table = tabulate(combined_summary, headers='keys', tablefmt='fancy_grid', floatfmt=".2f", numalign='center', stralign='center')
print(formatted_table)

conditions = [
    (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] <= thresholds[0]) & (df_positive['A_RENOUVELLE'] == False),
    (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] <= thresholds[0]) & (df_positive['A_RENOUVELLE'] == True),
    (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] > thresholds[0]) & (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] <= thresholds[1]) & (df_positive['A_RENOUVELLE'] == False),
    (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] > thresholds[0]) & (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] <= thresholds[1]) & (df_positive['A_RENOUVELLE'] == True),
    (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] > thresholds[1]) & (df_positive['A_RENOUVELLE'] == False),
    (df_positive['VALEUR_CLIENT'] > thresholds[1]) & (df_positive['A_RENOUVELLE'] == True)]

labels = [
    'Segment 1 - Churned', 
    'Segment 1 - Retained', 
    'Segment 2 - Churned', 
    'Segment 2 - Retained', 
    'Segment 3 - Churned', 
    'Segment 3 - Retained']

df_positive['Segment'] = np.select(conditions, labels, default='Unknown')
segment_summary = df_positive.groupby('Segment')['VALEUR_CLIENT'].agg(['count', 'mean']).rename(columns={'count': 'Nombre de Clients', 'mean': 'Valeur Client Moyenne'})
churn_summary = df_positive.groupby('Segment')['A_RENOUVELLE'].apply(lambda x: (x == False).mean()).rename('Taux de Churn')
combined_summary = segment_summary.join(churn_summary)
formatted_table = tabulate(combined_summary, headers='keys', tablefmt='fancy_grid', floatfmt=".2f", numalign='center', stralign='center')
print(formatted_table)
